Camera is too far away from the flowers. MotionMeerkat detects a movement in a leaf close to the camera all day and in the fotos objects flying around the inflorecences are visible occassionally, but with the resolution of the fotos I cannot even tell whether those are hummingbirds or insects.

We have two days of footage and there are plenty of hummingbird / flower contacts. Unfortunately the camera was placed too far away, so the MotionMeerkat detects only movements in the plants but not the hummingbird. Seeing the pictures in motion you can see the actual hummingbirds, but since they are so far away identification is difficult. I recognize Tawny-bellied and White-whiskered Hermit, but there maybe more species.
